{{DEFAULTSORT:Ashitaka}} [[Category:Background asteroids|006961]] [[Category:Discoveries by Makio Akiyama]] [[Category:Discoveries by Toshimasa Furuta]] [[Category:Minor planets named for places]] [[Category:Named minor planets]] [[Category:Astronomical objects discovered in 1989|19890526]]

'''Agawmeder''' was a historical state and region in the northwestern part of [[Ethiopia]]. Its most likely etymology is from ''Agew'' ([[Ge'ez language|Ge'ez]], አገው [[Agaw]]), a people living in the area, plus ''meder'' (land), thus meaning "Land of the Agaw".<ref>Uhlig, Siegbert, ed. ''Encyclopaedia Aethiopica: A-C''. Wiesbaden: Harrassowitz Verlag, 2003. p. 117</ref> The western neighbor of [[Gojjam]], it was located where the [[Agew Awi Zone]] now lies.

==History==
Not much is known about Agawmeder, as much of its existence was marked by Ethiopian isolation from the remainder of the world.<ref name="Encyclopaedia">Uhlig, Siegbert, ed. ''Encyclopaedia: A-C''. p. 142.</ref>

